snippet.textDisplay:
for those who don't know, jennie suffers from motion sickness, for those who don't know it is a type of disease that forces the body not to make many sudden movements. This disease has already made Jennifer suffer a lot on stage, meeting with fans and even in her daily life. and one of the main symptoms of this disease is nausea, drowsiness, cold sweat, headache and some other minor symptoms. don't blame jennie for something she didn't want to have to live in your life, don't blame her for being lazy, she's just paying for the consequences of moving too much.

#respectjennie

snippet.textDisplay: Wait, so why are people hating on Jeannie? As a person who only peripherally is aware of Blackpink, meaning I know a good amount of their music and have seen the house videos and random clips, I have no .  I know about her dating Kai, which seems like they might make a FANTASTIC couple because they're both understated and private people, along with being stupid hot, and I personally don't have any qualms with people in their 20's dating even though it may be seen as a scandal to some, (but to clarify, everyone has a right to their opinions and I understand I did not grow up in the Korean culture.) Additionally, from what I saw in the past, Jeannie seemed to be closest with Jisoo out of all of the girls in the group, but they all seemed great and like they got along. So I'm interested to see what all this is about. Last I checked (after SOLO came out,) Jeannie seemed to be Kpop's sweetheart
